  "prompt": "What is Roadrunner Technical Support?",
  "response": "Roadrunner Technical Support typically refers to technical assistance services related to Roadrunner Internet services, which were provided by Time Warner Cable and later became part of Spectrum after the merger with Charter Communications. This support can include help with various issues such as:\n\n1. **Internet Connectivity**: Resolving problems related to internet access, slow speeds, or outages.\n2. **Email Support**: Assistance with Roadrunner email accounts, including setup, password resets, and troubleshooting.\n3. **Equipment Issues**: Help with modems, routers, and other hardware related to the Roadrunner service.\n4. **Software Configuration**: Guidance on configuring devices to work with Roadrunner services, including computers, smartphones, and smart home devices.\n5. **Billing and Account Management**: Support for issues related to billing inquiries, account status, and subscription changes.\n\nWhile the Roadrunner brand is not widely used anymore, the support services have largely transitioned to the Spectrum brand, so you would typically seek support through Spectrum if you have services previously under Roadrunner.\n\nIf you need assistance, it's recommended to visit the official Spectrum website or contact Spectrum customer support directly.",
